Build a real-time karaoke and vocal recording system with the following complete feature set:
Input Sources:

Accept a YouTube URL and automatically download the beat/instrumental using yt-dlp (audio only, best quality)
Accept local MP3 or WAV file via drag-and-drop or file picker
Show waveform preview of the loaded beat

Key Detection & Autotune:

Automatically detect the musical key of the beat (e.g. C Major, A minor) using librosa pitch analysis
Display detected key and BPM in the UI
Real-time autotune on microphone input: snap vocal pitch to the nearest note in the detected key
Autotune intensity slider: 0% (dry) to 100% (hard tune / T-Pain effect)
Formant preservation so the voice doesn't sound robotic at low intensity

Real-time Vocal Effects Chain (applied live while singing):

Noise gate: suppress background noise below a threshold
Noise suppression / de-noise filter
EQ: 5-band parametric (sub, low, mid, high-mid, presence) with visual display
Compressor / limiter with threshold, ratio, attack, release controls
Echo / delay: tempo-synced to BPM with feedback and mix controls
Reverb: room size, damping, wet/dry mix
Vocal doubler / chorus effect
All effects toggleable on/off individually with bypass buttons

Playback & Recording:

Play the beat through speakers while capturing microphone input simultaneously
Mix beat + processed vocal in real-time (adjustable beat/vocal volume balance)
Record the final mixed output (beat + processed vocals) to a WAV file
Also option to record vocals-only (dry and/or processed) as separate track
Show live recording timer and waveform while recording
Export recorded file with filename and timestamp

UI Requirements:

Dark-themed professional audio workstation UI (DAW-style)
VU meters for input level, vocal level, and master output
Real-time pitch display showing current note being sung
Beat waveform timeline with playhead
All controls visible on one screen without scrolling (use panels/tabs if needed)
Keyboard shortcuts: Space = play/stop beat, R = start/stop recording, M = mute mic
 
Tech Stack:

Backend: Python with Flask, sounddevice for audio I/O, numpy for DSP, librosa for pitch/key detection, yt-dlp for YouTube download, scipy for filters
Frontend: Single HTML file with Web Audio API for visualization, WebSocket for real-time communication with backend
All dependencies listed in requirements.txt with pinned versions
README with setup instructions and how to run

Testing requirements:

Unit tests for key detection accuracy
Unit tests for each DSP effect function
Integration test: load a sample audio file, run key detection, verify output format
Test that Flask server starts and all API endpoints return correct status codes